		<description>Caliber: 7.63x25mm Mauser. 10-round internal mag. Semi-Automatic.
		
The Mauser C96 is a semi-automatic handgun designed by Fidel, Friedrich, and Josef Feederle in the 1890s. Produced initially by Mauser (and given its name by Paul Mauser himself) and later copied by many other entities, the C96 is iconic for being among the first widespread commercial semi-automatic handguns. Despite being acquired or tested in some form by almost every developed country at one point or another, the C96 pistol was never formally adopted by any military force; nevertheless, the C96 saw widespread use in military conflicts for over a half-century, and was also reasonably successful in private sales.</description>
